05/06/2005
PARIS, France -- Croatia defeated Bulgaria in a Group Eight World Cup qualifier in Sofia on Saturday (4 June), dealing an almost fatal blow to the home side's hopes of making it to the 2006 finals in Germany.
In other action Saturday, Macedonia beat Armenia 2-0 in Yerevan in Group One.
Romania lost to the Netherlands 2-0 in Rotterdam.
In Group Two, Greece held Turkey to a goalless draw in Istanbul, and Albania defeated Georgia 3-2 in Tirana.
In Group Seven, Bosnia and Herzegovina beat San Marino in Saravalle by 3-1, while Serbia-Montenegro had to settle for a goalless draw in its game with Belgium in Belgrade.
(AFP, Eurosport - 04/06/05)
